1
00:00:06,033 --> 00:00:09,333
Maybe it is better to
separate them for now

2
00:00:09,467 --> 00:00:10,533
while emotions
are still high.

3
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:14,167
The story is harder to control
if they are separated.

4
00:00:14,300 --> 00:00:16,067
Our marriage is dead.

5
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:17,500
So, do not hope
for a happy ending

6
00:00:17,633 --> 00:00:18,567
because it is already gone.

7
00:00:20,633 --> 00:00:22,500
That is karma for
the Torrecampos.

8
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:28,000
[FIRE CRACKLING]

9
00:00:28,133 --> 00:00:29,733
How the hell did this happen?

10
00:00:29,867 --> 00:00:30,867
[CLAMORING]

11
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:34,267
My jewelry collection is gone!

12
00:00:34,433 --> 00:00:37,067
I did not even save anything!

13
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:38,333
[CLAMORING]

14
00:00:38,467 --> 00:00:41,367
The CCTV was already down
before the fire started.

15
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:46,100
Who did this?

16
00:00:46,233 --> 00:00:47,767
Who?

17
00:00:47,900 --> 00:00:50,033
The mansion is a waste.

18
00:00:50,167 --> 00:00:52,733
That was supposed to be one
of your inheritances someday.

19
00:00:52,867 --> 00:00:56,233
<i>This house, this family,
should burn</i>

20
00:00:56,367 --> 00:00:58,133
<i> because this house is hell!</i>

21
00:01:45,267 --> 00:01:49,633
Marj, thank you for staying,
you and Jasmine.

22
00:01:49,767 --> 00:01:51,100
Do not thank me.

23
00:01:51,233 --> 00:01:52,833
I am not doing this for you.

24
00:01:54,933 --> 00:01:57,500
I am doing this for Jasmine.

25
00:01:57,633 --> 00:01:59,867
Our child is very fragile.

26
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,867
She can barely handle
the chemo anymore.

27
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:04,800
I do not want to add
more stress by leaving.

28
00:02:04,933 --> 00:02:06,233
And I will not risk her life

29
00:02:06,367 --> 00:02:09,233
just because I cannot stand
looking at your face.

30
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:12,033
I know.

31
00:02:13,067 --> 00:02:17,333
And I will never stop
until I make it up to you.

32
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:20,367
And I will do everything
to be deserving

33
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:21,567
of your second chance.

34
00:02:21,700 --> 00:02:22,933
Stop it.

35
00:02:23,067 --> 00:02:24,467
Do not talk about
second chances.

36
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:26,633
Let me be clear.

37
00:02:26,767 --> 00:02:28,233
We will live in the same house,

38
00:02:28,367 --> 00:02:30,900
but do not expect me
to be your wife.

39
00:02:31,033 --> 00:02:32,833
Nothing has changed.

40
00:02:32,967 --> 00:02:35,833
I will never forgive you, Paolo.

41
00:02:35,967 --> 00:02:38,267
Even if you kneel before me
every night,

42
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:40,700
what we had will never return.

43
00:02:40,833 --> 00:02:43,333
I am staying here for
our daughter's survival.

44
00:02:43,467 --> 00:02:45,667
And as far as I know
and am concerned,

45
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:47,233
our marriage is dead.

46
00:02:48,633 --> 00:02:50,000
So, do not hope
for a happy ending

47
00:02:50,133 --> 00:02:51,133
because it is already gone.

48
00:02:52,367 --> 00:02:56,433
[DRAMATIC]

49
00:03:18,167 --> 00:03:19,700
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

50
00:03:22,333 --> 00:03:24,967
Is what we are doing right?

51
00:03:25,100 --> 00:03:29,667
Do you think it is a wise idea
to keep them all under one roof?

52
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:31,567
We have other properties anyway.

53
00:03:31,700 --> 00:03:34,900
Maybe it is better
to separate them

54
00:03:35,033 --> 00:03:39,500
while emotions are still high.

55
00:03:39,733 --> 00:03:41,400
We have to contain
the situation.

56
00:03:43,267 --> 00:03:47,267
The story is harder to control
if they are separated.

57
00:03:48,767 --> 00:03:50,633
There will be
different versions.

58
00:03:51,167 --> 00:03:52,367
Total confusion.

59
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:55,200
And that is where our
destruction begins.

60
00:03:59,367 --> 00:04:01,567
We are already completely
damaged, Greg.

61
00:04:01,700 --> 00:04:04,167
We are being torn
apart on social media.

62
00:04:05,667 --> 00:04:07,433
Our reputation is ruined.

63
00:04:08,267 --> 00:04:10,333
Our name is ruined.

64
00:04:10,467 --> 00:04:12,033
Exactly.

65
00:04:12,167 --> 00:04:14,267
And do you know why?

66
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,767
Because of you.

67
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:18,267
I let you control me.

68
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:22,633
After I cheated with Evelyn,
I lost my way for a time.

69
00:04:22,767 --> 00:04:25,067
That is why I did
not foresee this.

70
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:27,167
I could have prevented this.

71
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:30,900
But I will not let
that happen again.

72
00:04:31,067 --> 00:04:32,500
Now that we are ruined,

73
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:36,700
you no longer have leverage
over me.

74
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:41,733
You can no longer hold me
hostage with a reputation

75
00:04:41,867 --> 00:04:42,967
that no longer exists.

76
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:46,667
[INTENSE]

77
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:49,167
But they still do not know
about you.

78
00:04:49,300 --> 00:04:53,367
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

79
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:54,267
That is right.

80
00:04:56,033 --> 00:04:58,733
So, before that happens,

81
00:04:58,867 --> 00:05:00,433
I will be the one in control
again.

82
00:05:02,867 --> 00:05:04,700
We will no longer
react to the shame.

83
00:05:05,700 --> 00:05:07,667
We will control the narrative.

84
00:05:09,167 --> 00:05:11,667
I will take back
control of this family.

85
00:05:12,900 --> 00:05:16,633
All of us will stay
together in this house,

86
00:05:16,767 --> 00:05:19,300
even if we suffer.

87
00:05:19,433 --> 00:05:21,867
As long as this family
stays together.

88
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:30,400
Fix your hair.

89
00:05:31,367 --> 00:05:39,933
[INTENSE]

90
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:46,033
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

91
00:05:46,167 --> 00:05:49,233
[INTENSE]

92
00:05:51,533 --> 00:05:53,867
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

93
00:05:58,133 --> 00:06:03,133
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

94
00:06:08,067 --> 00:06:12,867
[THRILLING]

95
00:06:15,033 --> 00:06:20,900
[THRILLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

96
00:06:33,933 --> 00:06:39,400
[THRILLING MUSIC]

97
00:06:45,367 --> 00:06:49,933
[THRILLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

98
00:06:59,300 --> 00:07:06,867
[SPEAKS IN VISAYAN LANGUAGE]

99
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:10,267
Things are still chaotic
in this house.

100
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:12,900
[SPEAKS IN VISAYAN LANGUAGE]

101
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:15,267
Thank you so much.

102
00:07:15,433 --> 00:07:20,933
[INTENSE]

103
00:07:22,033 --> 00:07:23,667
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

104
00:07:25,967 --> 00:07:27,733
[INTENSE]

105
00:07:34,467 --> 00:07:37,200
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

106
00:07:48,667 --> 00:07:55,733
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

107
00:08:05,933 --> 00:08:15,900
[FIRE CRACKLING]

108
00:08:18,267 --> 00:08:22,533
[FIRE ALARM BEEPING]

109
00:08:22,700 --> 00:08:27,533
[COUGHING]

110
00:08:27,667 --> 00:08:28,567
Jas?

111
00:08:28,700 --> 00:08:30,333
[COUGHING]

112
00:08:30,467 --> 00:08:31,233
Are you okay?

113
00:08:31,367 --> 00:08:35,500
[COUGHING]

114
00:08:35,633 --> 00:08:37,033
[JASMINE SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

115
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:42,633
Wait there. Stay right there.

116
00:08:42,767 --> 00:08:44,433
[COUGHING]

117
00:08:44,567 --> 00:08:46,200
Come here. Slowly.

118
00:08:46,333 --> 00:08:47,700
Marj, Jasmine,
the house is on fire!

119
00:08:47,833 --> 00:08:48,533
Come on!

120
00:08:48,667 --> 00:08:49,700
[COUGHING]

121
00:08:49,833 --> 00:08:54,300
[INTENSE]

122
00:08:57,700 --> 00:08:59,967
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

123
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:01,133
Ashley!

124
00:09:01,267 --> 00:09:04,500
[COUGHING]

125
00:09:04,633 --> 00:09:06,533
Ashley, my child!

126
00:09:06,667 --> 00:09:07,933
Let us go! Let us go!

127
00:09:08,067 --> 00:09:09,733
Hurry! Hurry!

128
00:09:09,867 --> 00:09:11,133
What is happening?

129
00:09:11,267 --> 00:09:12,467
[FIRE ALARM BEEPING]

130
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:13,667
What is happening?

131
00:09:15,067 --> 00:09:17,833
[INTENSE]

132
00:09:22,167 --> 00:09:24,433
[CLAMORING]

133
00:09:27,433 --> 00:09:30,900
[GLASS SHATTERS]

134
00:09:31,067 --> 00:09:34,267
[INTENSE]

135
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:37,567
[FIRE CRACKLING]

136
00:09:37,700 --> 00:09:40,833
[CLAMORING]

137
00:09:40,967 --> 00:09:44,900
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

138
00:09:48,733 --> 00:09:52,033
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

139
00:09:54,033 --> 00:09:58,500
[INTENSE]

140
00:10:13,700 --> 00:10:18,667
[FIRE TRUCK SIREN WAILING]

141
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:23,567
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

142
00:10:26,633 --> 00:10:29,267
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

143
00:10:32,733 --> 00:10:39,933
[INTENSE]

144
00:10:40,100 --> 00:10:42,467
How the hell did this happen?

145
00:10:43,967 --> 00:10:45,833
Who did this?

146
00:10:45,967 --> 00:10:48,400
Who?

147
00:10:48,533 --> 00:10:50,533
We do not know, Dad.

148
00:10:50,667 --> 00:10:55,867
But whoever is responsible,
we are going to make them pay.

149
00:10:58,633 --> 00:11:01,267
My jewelry collection is gone!

150
00:11:01,967 --> 00:11:04,967
I did not even save anything.

151
00:11:05,100 --> 00:11:07,200
Forget about it, Mom.

152
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,700
What matters is that
we are all safe.

153
00:11:11,900 --> 00:11:13,400
Jasmine, how are you feeling?

154
00:11:13,533 --> 00:11:14,500
Are you having trouble
breathing?

155
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:17,733
No, Mom. I am okay.

156
00:11:17,867 --> 00:11:18,733
Are you sure? Come on.

157
00:11:18,867 --> 00:11:20,067
I will take you
to the hospital.

158
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:21,467
Mom, I am fine.

159
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:33,067
[DRAMATIC]

160
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,500
[SOBBING]

161
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,200
Mom.

162
00:11:37,333 --> 00:11:38,533
Mom, please calm down.

163
00:11:38,667 --> 00:11:41,200
Everything is going to be
all right.

164
00:11:41,367 --> 00:11:42,267
Mom.

165
00:11:43,933 --> 00:11:45,133
What do you mean all right?

166
00:11:46,733 --> 00:11:48,767
The mansion is a waste.

167
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:52,233
That was supposed to be one
of your inheritances someday.

168
00:11:54,000 --> 00:12:03,967
[TENSE]

169
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:26,367
[SPEAKS IN VISAYAN LANGUAGE]

170
00:12:29,733 --> 00:12:30,867
All right.

171
00:12:31,267 --> 00:12:32,467
Thank you, Sir.

172
00:12:35,733 --> 00:12:38,033
If it was not faulty wiring,

173
00:12:38,167 --> 00:12:39,867
what could be the possible cause
of the fire?

174
00:12:40,967 --> 00:12:42,633
It is not conclusive.

175
00:12:42,767 --> 00:12:44,633
There were multiple ignition
points at the back,

176
00:12:44,767 --> 00:12:46,800
in the service area,
on the stairs,

177
00:12:46,933 --> 00:12:48,933
and on the ground floor.

178
00:12:49,100 --> 00:12:53,400
It could have been intentional,
but we still need to confirm it.

179
00:12:53,900 --> 00:12:55,633
Are you sure?

180
00:12:55,933 --> 00:12:57,167
We are still confirming, Sir.

181
00:12:58,367 --> 00:13:01,433
We also noticed that the CCTV
was already down

182
00:13:01,567 --> 00:13:03,267
before the fire started.

183
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:05,933
No footage was retrieved
from the cloud either.

184
00:13:06,233 --> 00:13:08,933
That is why we still cannot
track the entire incident.

185
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:15,500
<i>This house, this family,
should burn</i>

186
00:13:15,633 --> 00:13:17,433
<i> because this house is hell!</i>

187
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:24,367
[TENSE]

188
00:13:24,533 --> 00:13:25,733
Excuse me.

189
00:13:27,833 --> 00:13:32,400
Before the fire started,
I saw someone.

190
00:13:32,533 --> 00:13:34,167
They were wearing
a black hoodie.

191
00:13:34,300 --> 00:13:35,767
I was on the balcony then.

192
00:13:35,900 --> 00:13:37,800
I thought I was
just imagining it.

193
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:41,100
Are you sure, Ma'am?

194
00:13:41,233 --> 00:13:43,867
Yes, but they
suddenly disappeared.

195
00:13:46,167 --> 00:13:48,133
I will just take
your full statement.

196
00:13:49,133 --> 00:13:50,867
All right, I will take
care of Jasmine for now.

197
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:51,900
All right, Ma'am.

198
00:13:52,033 --> 00:13:54,433
You saw the person?

199
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:57,233
Well, Sir...

200
00:13:57,367 --> 00:14:03,300
[INTENSE]

201
00:14:06,633 --> 00:14:08,033
The kitchen items.

202
00:14:08,167 --> 00:14:10,400
Ma'am Regina's things.

203
00:14:10,533 --> 00:14:11,633
My God, Lord!

204
00:14:11,767 --> 00:14:13,200
There were still many
things inside,

205
00:14:13,333 --> 00:14:15,500
but some are already burned.

206
00:14:15,633 --> 00:14:16,700
Nanny!

207
00:14:16,833 --> 00:14:19,467
Nanny, our mansion is gone!

208
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:21,733
It has been burned
for a long time.

209
00:14:21,867 --> 00:14:23,733
We are only seeing it now.

210
00:14:24,733 --> 00:14:26,833
Nanny, where will we live now?

211
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:29,900
Good thing Cheche went
back to their place.

212
00:14:30,033 --> 00:14:32,200
Hopefully, she does not
come back.

213
00:14:32,333 --> 00:14:34,800
That is a sign that we all
need to leave this place.

214
00:14:35,967 --> 00:14:37,700
That is karma for
the Torrecampos.

215
00:14:38,700 --> 00:14:40,233
Ms. Yolly, do not be like that.

216
00:14:40,367 --> 00:14:41,533
Someone might hear us.

217
00:14:41,667 --> 00:14:43,967
When did they ever listen?

218
00:14:44,100 --> 00:14:46,667
Thank God I will finally
be gone from here.

219
00:14:50,833 --> 00:14:54,500
I do not need to
see what burns next.

220
00:14:57,900 --> 00:15:03,100
[INTENSE]

221
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:12,300
Oh, it is almost sunrise.

222
00:15:12,433 --> 00:15:14,533
I want this to be over.

223
00:15:14,667 --> 00:15:16,000
I want to go home.

224
00:15:16,133 --> 00:15:18,467
What? Is it not over yet?

225
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:21,600
Ma'am, the investigators
still have many questions.

226
00:15:21,733 --> 00:15:23,333
They said we cannot leave yet.

227
00:15:23,467 --> 00:15:26,000
I want to leave.

228
00:15:27,667 --> 00:15:29,300
Mom, coffee.

229
00:15:29,433 --> 00:15:30,533
Thank you, my child.

230
00:15:35,233 --> 00:15:36,433
Ash, juice.

231
00:15:39,967 --> 00:15:40,933
Thank you.

232
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:44,733
I am done giving my statement.

233
00:15:44,867 --> 00:15:45,800
And I heard from Mom

234
00:15:45,933 --> 00:15:48,967
that we are moving to your house
in the South.

235
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:50,133
Should we go ahead first?

236
00:15:51,133 --> 00:15:52,267
[EDWARD SCOFFS]

237
00:15:59,367 --> 00:16:01,267
[EXCLAIMS]

238
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:02,400
Dad!

239
00:16:02,533 --> 00:16:03,333
Greg!

240
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:05,133
Greg, what is it?

241
00:16:05,267 --> 00:16:06,933
Was this you?

242
00:16:07,067 --> 00:16:08,033
What?

243
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:12,000
Did you do this?

244
00:16:12,133 --> 00:16:13,467
Did you do this on purpose?

245
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:14,567
Wait, Dad.

246
00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:15,700
Hold on.

247
00:16:15,833 --> 00:16:17,833
I am angry at our family,
Dad, yes.

248
00:16:18,167 --> 00:16:19,667
But you are wrong.

249
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:21,400
I did not do this.

250
00:16:21,533 --> 00:16:26,133
But it seems someone else
is even angrier at our family.

251
00:16:28,133 --> 00:16:31,267
Make sure you are
telling the truth.

252
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:33,467
Because if I find out
you were involved,

253
00:16:36,133 --> 00:16:37,400
I will have you jailed.

254
00:16:37,533 --> 00:16:39,733
Greg, that is enough!

255
00:16:39,867 --> 00:16:44,200
[INTENSE]

256
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:03,400
Weng, please put my things
in Jasmine's room for now, okay?

257
00:17:03,667 --> 00:17:04,567
All right, Ma'am.

258
00:17:04,700 --> 00:17:06,567
But Ma'am, not in your room
with Sir Paolo?

259
00:17:08,633 --> 00:17:10,167
Can you just follow me,

260
00:17:10,300 --> 00:17:12,600
and you take care of Jasmine
for now?

261
00:17:12,733 --> 00:17:14,800
I need to visit my sibling
at the hospital.

262
00:17:14,967 --> 00:17:16,467
All right, Ma'am.

263
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:17,367
Hey, the things.

264
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:18,300
Hurry up.

265
00:17:19,600 --> 00:17:20,700
Hi, Marj.

266
00:17:22,933 --> 00:17:24,467
How is Jobert doing?

267
00:17:24,600 --> 00:17:26,500
Is there still hope
that they will wake up?

268
00:17:26,633 --> 00:17:29,733
Can you not pretend to
be concerned about my sibling?

269
00:17:29,867 --> 00:17:32,500
Because it does not suit someone
as fake and venomous as you.

270
00:17:32,633 --> 00:17:33,400
[HUFFS]

271
00:17:33,533 --> 00:17:34,467
Wow!

272
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:36,200
The way you talk,

273
00:17:36,333 --> 00:17:38,200
it is like you know me so well.

274
00:17:38,333 --> 00:17:40,400
As if you have me
all figured out.

275
00:17:40,533 --> 00:17:42,800
Why? Are you still hiding
something from me?

276
00:17:42,933 --> 00:17:44,300
Is there something
I still do not know?

277
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:48,533
[CHUCKLES]

278
00:17:48,700 --> 00:17:49,833
You know what, Marj,

279
00:17:49,967 --> 00:17:52,433
you should just stick
to your plan.

280
00:17:52,567 --> 00:17:54,400
Move out with your child.

281
00:17:54,533 --> 00:17:58,367
Because let us face it,
even if you see me as a snake,

282
00:17:58,500 --> 00:18:01,500
I am still the apple
of our in-laws' eyes.

283
00:18:01,633 --> 00:18:02,867
Who said so?

284
00:18:04,567 --> 00:18:05,467
[CHUCKLES]

285
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:08,100
How dare you speak to Marjorie
that way?

286
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:13,133
Mom, Marj just has...

287
00:18:13,267 --> 00:18:14,433
Shut up!

288
00:18:18,367 --> 00:18:22,133
After everything,
after all the humiliation,

289
00:18:22,300 --> 00:18:25,100
we chose to endure you
for the children.

290
00:18:25,233 --> 00:18:27,267
And this is what you do to Marj?

291
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:29,700
Do not abuse our patience, Thea.

292
00:18:31,300 --> 00:18:33,633
I was just asking her
about her plans.

293
00:18:36,067 --> 00:18:37,267
You want to stay here?

294
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:40,900
Then learn your place.

295
00:18:41,033 --> 00:18:42,800
If you cause trouble here again,

296
00:18:42,933 --> 00:18:47,033
I will personally drag you out
of this house.

297
00:18:47,167 --> 00:18:52,767
[INTENSE]

298
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:06,100
[PENSIVE]

299
00:19:06,233 --> 00:19:07,167
Mom.

300
00:19:08,900 --> 00:19:10,100
Mom, thank you.

301
00:19:11,633 --> 00:19:14,167
I did not expect you to side
with me.

302
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:20,233
I am angry at Thea because
she had an affair with Paolo.

303
00:19:20,367 --> 00:19:24,667
She destroyed any chance left
for my children to reconcile.

304
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:26,867
But as much as I hate her
right now,

305
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,400
I still have not forgotten that
you brought your mother here,

306
00:19:29,567 --> 00:19:31,400
and she destroyed my marriage.

307
00:19:31,533 --> 00:19:34,033
So, if we are being honest,

308
00:19:34,167 --> 00:19:35,533
you and Thea are both
responsible

309
00:19:35,667 --> 00:19:37,533
for the destruction
of my family.

310
00:19:37,667 --> 00:19:40,400
Mom, my mother already
regretted that.

311
00:19:40,533 --> 00:19:44,200
And please do not blame me
for the mistakes of others.

312
00:19:44,333 --> 00:19:47,100
I am not blaming you
for her choices.

313
00:19:47,233 --> 00:19:51,167
But you cannot deny that
you were complicit.

314
00:19:51,300 --> 00:19:53,633
You decided to stay silent.

315
00:19:53,767 --> 00:19:56,667
So do not expect me now
to be loud and welcoming.

316
00:19:56,800 --> 00:20:00,233
[INTENSE]

317
00:20:00,367 --> 00:20:02,967
Do not think that
just because I silenced Thea,

318
00:20:03,133 --> 00:20:04,767
we are on the same side.

319
00:20:05,667 --> 00:20:09,533
No, I just chose
the lesser evil, Marj.

320
00:20:13,100 --> 00:20:20,567
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

321
00:20:27,900 --> 00:20:29,600
Edward.

322
00:20:29,733 --> 00:20:31,967
Marj, sorry,
I was just passing by.

323
00:20:34,167 --> 00:20:35,700
I do not really have
anywhere else to go.

324
00:20:35,867 --> 00:20:41,200
[DRAMATIC]

325
00:20:41,433 --> 00:20:44,200
This feels like
the only quiet place.

326
00:20:44,333 --> 00:20:48,767
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

327
00:20:54,100 --> 00:20:55,500
You know that feeling when...

328
00:20:58,267 --> 00:21:00,133
in an instant,

329
00:21:02,133 --> 00:21:04,033
everything you thought
was certain disappears.

330
00:21:05,867 --> 00:21:07,433
I thought Thea was the one.

331
00:21:09,133 --> 00:21:12,800
Even though I was not sure
about her,

332
00:21:12,933 --> 00:21:13,967
I forced it.

333
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,900
I convinced myself...

334
00:21:19,700 --> 00:21:23,400
that she was the right person
to spend my life with.

335
00:21:26,767 --> 00:21:27,933
I do not know...

336
00:21:29,767 --> 00:21:31,433
it feels like I am slowly losing
my grip on reality

337
00:21:31,567 --> 00:21:33,333
after everything
that has happened.

338
00:21:33,467 --> 00:21:38,433
[DRAMATIC]

339
00:21:50,567 --> 00:21:51,833
Marj, I am sorry.

340
00:21:54,733 --> 00:21:56,167
I should not be bothering you.

341
00:21:57,967 --> 00:22:01,000
But I feel like you are
the only one

342
00:22:01,133 --> 00:22:02,867
who can understand how I feel.

343
00:22:04,700 --> 00:22:06,167
You are not alone.

344
00:22:13,733 --> 00:22:15,433
I feel like a failure.

345
00:22:19,433 --> 00:22:22,500
I am close to admitting

346
00:22:22,633 --> 00:22:24,500
that Dad has been right
all along.

347
00:22:28,567 --> 00:22:29,667
No.

348
00:22:31,333 --> 00:22:34,233
You were hurt and deceived,

349
00:22:34,367 --> 00:22:35,933
but you are not a failure

350
00:22:36,067 --> 00:22:37,900
because you still have a child.

351
00:22:42,100 --> 00:22:43,467
Ashley.

352
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:48,933
She is the only one
I can be proud of.

353
00:22:52,333 --> 00:22:53,667
She is all I have left.

354
00:22:54,433 --> 00:22:56,333
Being a father is...

355
00:22:58,067 --> 00:22:59,400
that's all I have left.

356
00:23:00,500 --> 00:23:08,500
[DRAMATIC]

357
00:23:08,633 --> 00:23:10,633
You need to be strong.

358
00:23:12,100 --> 00:23:13,933
Your child needs you.

359
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:19,600
Just like what I am doing
for Jasmine and for Jobert.

360
00:23:22,633 --> 00:23:25,067
But sometimes,
it really gets exhausting.

361
00:23:27,133 --> 00:23:31,333
Because who do we lean on
if not people like us, right?

362
00:23:31,467 --> 00:23:33,200
The ones who have
to stay strong.

363
00:23:36,700 --> 00:23:40,133
[PHONE RINGING]

364
00:23:40,267 --> 00:23:41,467
[SIGHS]

365
00:23:44,200 --> 00:23:47,167
Why? Edward, is there a problem?

366
00:23:47,300 --> 00:23:49,967
This is my contact who has been
looking for your mother.

367
00:23:51,833 --> 00:23:52,867
Hello?

368
00:23:54,100 --> 00:23:55,067
What?

369
00:23:56,033 --> 00:23:57,300
Are you sure?

370
00:23:58,300 --> 00:23:59,333
Is she with you?

371
00:23:59,467 --> 00:24:05,867
[INTENSE]

372
00:24:09,367 --> 00:24:10,433
Mom.

373
00:24:10,567 --> 00:24:13,267
[DRAMATIC]

374
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:14,733
Mom...

375
00:24:14,867 --> 00:24:15,800
Mom...

376
00:24:17,767 --> 00:24:20,100
[SOBBING]

377
00:24:32,333 --> 00:24:33,100
Marj...

378
00:24:33,233 --> 00:24:35,733
[SPEAKS IN VISAYAN LANGUAGE]

379
00:24:37,633 --> 00:24:39,067
Sorry, Marj.

380
00:24:39,200 --> 00:24:40,133
It is okay.

381
00:24:40,267 --> 00:24:41,367
It is okay, Mom.

382
00:24:43,200 --> 00:24:48,767
[GINA SPEAKS
IN VISAYAN LANGUAGE]

383
00:24:48,900 --> 00:24:53,500
[MARJ SPEAKS
IN VISAYAN LANGUAGE]

384
00:24:55,600 --> 00:24:57,867
It is a good thing
Edward found you.

385
00:24:58,733 --> 00:24:59,700
If he had not found you,

386
00:24:59,833 --> 00:25:01,700
you would not have known
what happened to Jobert.

387
00:25:01,867 --> 00:25:03,333
Exactly, Marj.

388
00:25:03,467 --> 00:25:06,267
I am truly very grateful to him.

389
00:25:09,700 --> 00:25:11,667
How is your sibling now?

390
00:25:13,567 --> 00:25:16,467
They are still not waking up,
Mom, but they are fighting.

391
00:25:19,367 --> 00:25:20,500
And you?

392
00:25:22,367 --> 00:25:23,300
The same.

393
00:25:23,433 --> 00:25:24,633
Just the same.

394
00:25:27,333 --> 00:25:30,933
[SOBBING]

395
00:25:32,433 --> 00:25:39,567
[DRAMATIC]

396
00:25:42,967 --> 00:25:44,067
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

397
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:45,333
Everything could fall apart

398
00:25:45,467 --> 00:25:47,533
because of you
and Thea's recklessness.

399
00:25:47,667 --> 00:25:48,600
You did not know
how to be careful.

400
00:25:48,733 --> 00:25:51,933
Marj has opened a Pandora's Box.

401
00:25:52,067 --> 00:25:53,567
And you know what that means,

402
00:25:53,700 --> 00:25:57,533
the things we hid before
will all come out.

403
00:25:57,667 --> 00:26:01,500
I saw Kind Brother
and Sister Thea.

404
00:26:01,633 --> 00:26:05,533
I told on you, Sis,
and then she let go.

405
00:26:05,667 --> 00:26:07,067
She really let go of you?

406
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:08,933
Yes.

407
00:26:09,100 --> 00:26:10,500
That is your shameless
mistress right there.

408
00:26:10,633 --> 00:26:11,633
I know nothing about that.

409
00:26:11,767 --> 00:26:13,133
I am telling you the truth.

410
00:26:13,267 --> 00:26:15,267
You have lied to me
so many times.

411
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:16,967
Are you still hiding something?

412
00:26:17,100 --> 00:26:18,633
What do you think
will happen

413
00:26:18,767 --> 00:26:21,067
when Marj finds out you have
been lying for a long time

414
00:26:21,200 --> 00:26:22,267
about Ashley?

415
00:26:22,400 --> 00:26:23,167
Your child.

416
00:26:23,300 --> 00:26:24,633
That would be a much
bigger scandal.

417
00:26:24,767 --> 00:26:26,567
It will not just
affect the family.

418
00:26:26,700 --> 00:26:28,833
You knew! But you never told me!

419
00:26:28,967 --> 00:26:31,267
But instead, you protected
your golden child,

420
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:35,733
perfect and flawless in front of
others, at my expense!

421
00:26:35,867 --> 00:26:39,267
You know what, you are
a completely worthless father!

422
00:26:40,233 --> 00:26:41,400
[THUDS]

423
00:26:41,533 --> 00:26:43,900
[INTENSE]
